        "answer": "A",
        "explanation": "The signs are +, -, +, -. There are 3 sign changes, so possible positive zeros = 3 or 1."
      },
      {
        "type": "mcq",
        "question": "Solve $\\frac{3}{x+2} + \\frac{1}{x-2} = \\frac{4}{x^2-4}$.",
